9th International Conference on Statistical Analysis of Textual Data 
Short Title: JADT 2008 

Date: 12-Mar-2008 - 14-Mar-2008 
Location: Lyon, France 
Contact: Serge Heiden 
Contact Email: jadt2008@ens-lsh.fr 
Meeting URL: http://jadt.org 

Meeting Description: 

The 9th International Conference on the Statistical Analysis of Textual
Data will be held in Lyon (France), on March 12-14, 2008. 

JADT 2008 - Call for Participation

9th International Conference on the Statistical Analysis of Textual Data

March 12 - 14 2008
at Ecole normale supérieure
Lettres et sciences humaines
Lyon, France

http://www.jadt.org/

The  9th  International  Conference  on the  Statistical  Analysis  of
Textual  Data will be  held in  Lyon (France),  on March  12-14, 2008.
This  biennial  conference,  which  has  constantly  been  gaining  in
importance since its first occurrence  in Barcelona (1990), is open to
all  scholars and  researchers working  in the  field of  textual data
analysis,  ranging  from lexicography  to  the  analysis of  political
discourse,  from  information retrieval  to  marketing research,  from
computational  linguistics to  sociolinguistics, from  text  mining to
content  analysis. After  the success  of the  previous  meetings, the
three-day conference in Lyon will continue to provide a workshop-style
forum  through  technical paper  sessions,  invited  talks, and  panel
discussions.

Registration

Registration forms are available on the site :
http://jadt2008.ens-lsh.fr/spip.php?rubrique10&lang=en
Early bird registration fees end February 8, 2008.

Registration Fee

Registration for the JADT 2008 conference includes:
- attendance to all sessions of the conference
- a paper copy of the proceedings of JADT 2008
- the cocktail reception
- 3 lunch at the CROUS restaurant at ENS Lyon
- coffee breaks

In addition to the main registration, you are invited to register for the
conference banquet to be held Thursday, March 13 in the evening (the
banquet should be along the Saone river on the Hermès restaurant boat). The
price is 40 euros.

[Note: from March 1, registration for the banquet is closed]

Rates

Registration before Friday, February 8, 2008
      [Note: Payments must be effective prior to 8/2/2008]
          Full price: 180 Euros (professor, researcher, post-doc, commercial)
          Reduced rate: 100 Euros (student, unemployed)
Registration after Friday, February 8, 2008
          Full price: 250 Euros
          Reduced rate: 150 Euros
Banquet extra: 40 Euros

